{
  "stem": "22979.6",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And then everything freezes on you.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Many had freezing noses, frozen toes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I didn't dare take off my shoes, wet shoes, because I wouldn't be able to put them back.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "The, the stockings were wet, everything was wet.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Finally, we came to rest in one farm, big farm, where it was straw.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So we rested there for a while, then we continued until we came to a city-- to a, to, to a train station, which was Loslau.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "I don't know how the city is now named because it belongs to Poland.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "It was a part of Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "That was already the border of Germany.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Then they loaded us in open coal, coal carriages, or how you call  it, coal wagons-- open.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And it was snowing and winter.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Some of the girls could go to the engine who pulled the train, and hot water was dropping.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Other was nothing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "They squeezed 100 of us in one open cattle car.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "[SIGHS] We had room only to stand, and freezing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Many of the inmates died there, so we just throw them out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "Naturally, took everything which was usable away from them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "I don't know how long we traveled.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "I can't tell you.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "But the hunger-- you don't know, who was not in a situation, how hunger hurts.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [SOBBING] It's worse than a disease.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "Hunger hurts very much.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "This time I promised myself, if I ever survive, and I get home, and I live a normal life, and maybe I get once married, and I have a family, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] they never, ever will know what hunger means.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "[SOBBING] I didn't dream of too much, only to have a roof and to have what to eat.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
